Explanation:
We use a 2D dynamic programming table to store the minimum number of characters to be changed to form a palindrome substring starting from index i and ending at index i + k - 1. We iterate through the string once to fill the dp table and then iterate through the string again to find the maximum value in the dp table at index i. The final result is the maximum value in the dp table at index i.

